ue keeping the real world as a seperate thing, and expect members and recruits to respect those that wish to be more immersive into the roleplay enviroment.<br><br>Lex members are expected to be patient, supportive, proactive and in general team players.  While we are recruiting, it's important to remember that as a guild we would rather see team players join the family, and if you aren't a team player or willing to show a bit of effort when it comes to applying and participating, you likely won't be compatible.<br><br>We are focusing on becoming stronger and streamlined and although we very much value hunting and are generaly pvping in groups in many locations, patience is a mandatory.  We are not a guild that places being Uber over being a solid family.  If Uber comes, then so be it, but it won't be through any single minded vision of tossing all other aspects of the game out the door to get there.<br><br>In short, we welcome new players, but our goals are to have additions to the family that don't just warm seats, but instead fill slots that enhance the guild as a whole. <br><br>If you feel you might be someone that would appreciate this sort of familial guild, then by all means, come apply.  Our level requirement is currently 40 but might be raised to 45 since 40 is lower than our average (we tend to be low to mid 50's high 40's). We do make exceptions to this if people make characters with the explicit intention of being part of the Lex family or if we happen upon young darklings that show extreme promise of being a Lex type of person.  For this we provide a fosterling program where one of the higher levels acts as a mentor to your character and is responsible for you and your needs until you hit level 30.  For our fosterlings, we work hard at equipping them with items that while not uber, will help considerably when it comes to speeding through the levels to catch up to the current active range.  We also provide power leveling, though this is a courtesy and should be seen as such.<br><br>If you are interested in learning more, or would like to apply, please visit our Ezboard by clicking on the link below my sig file that is titled 'Lex Invictus'.  Look forward to seeing you! <p><CENTER><HR WIDTH=250><FONT COLOR="RED" FACE="ARIAL"><B><I>Cute little cup-cake, baked by the devil!</I></B></FONT><BR><img src="http://www.pbbr.com/test/synnsig.jpg"><br><A HREF="http://synnovea.no-frills.net"><font face="ARIAL">Phasmatis ex Machina</font></a><BR><a href="http://pub78.ezboard.com/bsansplace1476"><font face="ARIAL">Lex Invictus Bulletin Board</font></a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub77.ezboard.com/usynnoveaeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SynnoveaEQ</A> at: 11/7/01 8:28:34 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub77.ezboard.com/ugildisdhorentath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gildis Dhorentath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 535<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(10/12/01 6:00:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub77.ezboard.com/ftallonzektimes4735guildsoftallonzek.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lex Invictus Recruiting</span><hr size=1> You guys should merge with Second Rising. RP taking Kunark back.  <p><BR>Gildis Dhorentath<BR>Iksar Necromancer<BR>Second Rising</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub77.ezboard.com/umalwae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>malwae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Thief of Hearts</span><br>  Posts: 1600<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(10/12/01 12:48:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub77.ezboard.com/ftallonzektimes4735guildsoftallonzek.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/atsila/pictures/Malsig.jpg 